34class TypeBase {
35 public:
36 enum class Kind {
37 kTopType,
38 kAbstractType,
39 kBuiltinPointerType,
40 kUnionType,
41 kBitFieldStructType,
42 kStructType,
43 kClassType
44 };
45 virtual ~TypeBase() = default;
46 bool IsTopType() const { return kind() == Kind::kTopType; }
47 bool IsAbstractType() const { return kind() == Kind::kAbstractType; }
48 bool IsBuiltinPointerType() const {
49 return kind() == Kind::kBuiltinPointerType;
50 }
51 bool IsUnionType() const { return kind() == Kind::kUnionType; }
52 bool IsBitFieldStructType() const {
53 return kind() == Kind::kBitFieldStructType;
54 }
55 bool IsStructType() const { return kind() == Kind::kStructType; }
56 bool IsClassType() const { return kind() == Kind::kClassType; }
57 bool IsAggregateType() const { return IsStructType() || IsClassType(); }
58
59 protected:
60 explicit TypeBase(Kind kind) : kind_(kind) {}
61 Kind kind() const { return kind_; }
62
63 private:
64 const Kind kind_;
65};
66
67#define DECLARE_TYPE_BOILERPLATE(x) \
68 static x* cast(TypeBase* declarable) { \
69 DCHECK(declarable->Is##x()); \
70 return static_cast<x*>(declarable); \
71 } \
72 static const x* cast(const TypeBase* declarable) { \
73 DCHECK(declarable->Is##x()); \
74 return static_cast<const x*>(declarable); \
75 } \
76 static x* DynamicCast(TypeBase* declarable) { \
77 if (!declarable) return nullptr; \
78 if (!declarable->Is##x()) return nullptr; \
79 return static_cast<x*>(declarable); \
80 } \
81 static const x* DynamicCast(const TypeBase* declarable) { \
82 if (!declarable) return nullptr; \
83 if (!declarable->Is##x()) return nullptr; \
84 return static_cast<const x*>(declarable); \
85 }

95using MaybeSpecializationKey = base::Optional<SpecializationKey<GenericType>>;

97struct TypeChecker {
98 // The type of the object. This string is not guaranteed to correspond to a
99 // C++ class, but just to a type checker function: for any type "Foo" here,
100 // the function IsFoo must exist.
101 std::string type;
102 // If {type} is "MaybeObject", then {weak_ref_to} indicates the corresponding
103 // strong object type. Otherwise, {weak_ref_to} is empty.
104 std::string weak_ref_to;
105};

107class V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE Type : public TypeBase {
108 public:
109 Type& operator=(const Type& other) = delete;
110 virtual bool IsSubtypeOf(const Type* supertype) const;
111
112 // Default rendering for error messages etc.
113 std::string ToString() const;
114
115 // This name is not unique, but short and somewhat descriptive.
116 // Used for naming generated code.
117 virtual std::string SimpleName() const;
118
119 enum class HandleKind { kIndirect, kDirect };
120 std::string GetHandleTypeName(HandleKind kind,
121 const std::string& type_name) const;
122
123 std::string TagglifiedCppTypeName() const;
124 std::string HandlifiedCppTypeName(HandleKind kind) const;
125
126 const Type* parent() const { return parent_; }
127 bool IsVoid() const { return IsAbstractName(VOID_TYPE_STRING); }
128 bool IsNever() const { return IsAbstractName(NEVER_TYPE_STRING); }
129 bool IsBool() const { return IsAbstractName(BOOL_TYPE_STRING); }
130 bool IsConstexprBool() const {
131 return IsAbstractName(CONSTEXPR_BOOL_TYPE_STRING);
132 }
133 bool IsVoidOrNever() const { return IsVoid() || IsNever(); }
134 bool IsFloat32() const { return IsAbstractName(FLOAT32_TYPE_STRING); }
135 bool IsFloat64() const { return IsAbstractName(FLOAT64_TYPE_STRING); }
136 std::string GetGeneratedTypeName() const;
137 std::string GetGeneratedTNodeTypeName() const;
138 virtual bool IsConstexpr() const {
139 if (parent()) DCHECK(!parent()->IsConstexpr());
140 return false;
141 }
142 virtual bool IsTransient() const { return false; }
143 virtual const Type* NonConstexprVersion() const { return this; }
144 std::string GetConstexprGeneratedTypeName() const;
145 base::Optional<const ClassType*> ClassSupertype() const;
146 base::Optional<const StructType*> StructSupertype() const;
147 base::Optional<const AggregateType*> AggregateSupertype() const;
148 virtual std::vector<TypeChecker> GetTypeCheckers() const { return {}; }
149 virtual std::string GetRuntimeType() const;
150 virtual std::string GetDebugType() const;
151 static const Type* CommonSupertype(const Type* a, const Type* b);
152 void AddAlias(std::string alias) const { aliases_.insert(std::move(alias)); }
153 size_t id() const { return id_; }
154 const MaybeSpecializationKey& GetSpecializedFrom() const {
155 return specialized_from_;
156 }
157
158 static base::Optional<const Type*> MatchUnaryGeneric(const Type* type,
159 GenericType* generic);
160
161 static std::string ComputeName(const std::string& basename,
162 MaybeSpecializationKey specialized_from);
163 virtual void SetConstexprVersion(const Type* type) const {
164 constexpr_version_ = type;
165 }
166
167 virtual const Type* ConstexprVersion() const {
168 if (constexpr_version_) return constexpr_version_;
169 if (IsConstexpr()) return this;
170 if (parent()) return parent()->ConstexprVersion();
171 return nullptr;
172 }
173
174 virtual size_t AlignmentLog2() const;
175
176 protected:
177 Type(TypeBase::Kind kind, const Type* parent,
178 MaybeSpecializationKey specialized_from = base::nullopt);
179 Type(const Type& other) V8_NOEXCEPT;
180 void set_parent(const Type* t) { parent_ = t; }
181 int Depth() const;
182 virtual std::string ToExplicitString() const = 0;
183 virtual std::string GetGeneratedTypeNameImpl() const = 0;
184 virtual std::string GetGeneratedTNodeTypeNameImpl() const = 0;
185 virtual std::string SimpleNameImpl() const = 0;
186
187 private:
188 bool IsAbstractName(const std::string& name) const;
189
190 // If {parent_} is not nullptr, then this type is a subtype of {parent_}.
191 const Type* parent_;
192 mutable std::set<std::string> aliases_;
193 size_t id_;
194 MaybeSpecializationKey specialized_from_;
195 mutable const Type* constexpr_version_ = nullptr;
196};

198inline size_t hash_value(const TypeVector& types) {
199 size_t hash = 0;
200 for (const Type* t : types) {
201 hash = base::hash_combine(hash, t);
202 }
203 return hash;
204}

213struct Field {
214 // TODO(danno): This likely should be refactored, the handling of the types
215 // using the universal grab-bag utility with std::tie, as well as the
216 // reliance of string types is quite clunky.
217 std::tuple<size_t, std::string> GetFieldSizeInformation() const;
218
219 void ValidateAlignment(ResidueClass at_offset) const;
220
221 SourcePosition pos;
222 const AggregateType* aggregate;
223 base::Optional<ClassFieldIndexInfo> index;
224 NameAndType name_and_type;
225
226 // The byte offset of this field from the beginning of the containing class or
227 // struct. Most structs are never packed together in memory, and are only used
228 // to hold a batch of related CSA TNode values, in which case |offset| is
229 // irrelevant.
230 // The offset may be unknown because the field is after an indexed field or
231 // because we don't support the struct field for on-heap layouts.
232 base::Optional<size_t> offset;
233
234 bool custom_weak_marking;
235 bool const_qualified;
236 FieldSynchronization read_synchronization;
237 FieldSynchronization write_synchronization;
238};
239
240std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream& os, const Field& name_and_type);

242class TopType final : public Type {
243 public:
244 DECLARE_TYPE_BOILERPLATE(TopType)
245 std::string GetGeneratedTypeNameImpl() const override { UNREACHABLE(); }
246 std::string GetGeneratedTNodeTypeNameImpl() const override {
247 return source_type_->GetGeneratedTNodeTypeName();
248 }
249 std::string ToExplicitString() const override {
250 std::stringstream s;
251 s << "inaccessible " + source_type_->ToString();
252 return s.str();
253 }
254
255 const Type* source_type() const { return source_type_; }
256 const std::string reason() const { return reason_; }
257
258 private:
259 friend class TypeOracle;
260 explicit TopType(std::string reason, const Type* source_type)
261 : Type(Kind::kTopType, nullptr),
262 reason_(std::move(reason)),
263 source_type_(source_type) {}
264 std::string SimpleNameImpl() const override { return "TopType"; }
265
266 std::string reason_;
267 const Type* source_type_;
268};

270class AbstractType final : public Type {
271 public:
272 DECLARE_TYPE_BOILERPLATE(AbstractType)
273 const std::string& name() const { return name_; }
274 std::string ToExplicitString() const override { return name(); }
275 std::string GetGeneratedTypeNameImpl() const override;
276 std::string GetGeneratedTNodeTypeNameImpl() const override;
277 bool IsConstexpr() const final {
278 const bool is_constexpr = flags_ & AbstractTypeFlag::kConstexpr;
279 DCHECK_IMPLIES(non_constexpr_version_ != nullptr, is_constexpr);
280 return is_constexpr;
281 }
282
283 const Type* NonConstexprVersion() const override {
284 if (non_constexpr_version_) return non_constexpr_version_;
285 if (!IsConstexpr()) return this;
286 if (parent()) return parent()->NonConstexprVersion();
287 return nullptr;
288 }
289
290 std::vector<TypeChecker> GetTypeCheckers() const override;
291
292 size_t AlignmentLog2() const override;
293
294 private:
295 friend class TypeOracle;
296 AbstractType(const Type* parent, AbstractTypeFlags flags,
297 const std::string& name, const std::string& generated_type,
298 const Type* non_constexpr_version,
299 MaybeSpecializationKey specialized_from)
300 : Type(Kind::kAbstractType, parent, specialized_from),
301 flags_(flags),
302 name_(name),
303 generated_type_(generated_type),
304 non_constexpr_version_(non_constexpr_version) {
305 if (parent) DCHECK_EQ(parent->IsConstexpr(), IsConstexpr());
306 DCHECK_EQ(IsConstexprName(name), IsConstexpr());
307 DCHECK_IMPLIES(non_constexpr_version_ != nullptr, IsConstexpr());
308 DCHECK(!(IsConstexpr() && (flags_ & AbstractTypeFlag::kTransient)));
309 }
310
311 std::string SimpleNameImpl() const override {
312 if (IsConstexpr()) {
313 const Type* non_constexpr_version = NonConstexprVersion();
314 if (non_constexpr_version == nullptr) {
315 ReportError("Cannot find non-constexpr type corresponding to ", *this);
316 }
317 return "constexpr_" + non_constexpr_version->SimpleName();
318 }
319 return name();
320 }
321
322 bool IsTransient() const override {
323 return flags_ & AbstractTypeFlag::kTransient;
324 }
325
326 bool UseParentTypeChecker() const {
327 return flags_ & AbstractTypeFlag::kUseParentTypeChecker;
328 }
329
330 AbstractTypeFlags flags_;
331 const std::string name_;
332 const std::string generated_type_;
333 const Type* non_constexpr_version_;
334};

336// For now, builtin pointers are restricted to Torque-defined builtins.
337class V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE BuiltinPointerType final : public Type {
338 public:
339 DECLARE_TYPE_BOILERPLATE(BuiltinPointerType)
340 std::string ToExplicitString() const override;
341 std::string GetGeneratedTypeNameImpl() const override {
342 return parent()->GetGeneratedTypeName();
343 }
344 std::string GetGeneratedTNodeTypeNameImpl() const override {
345 return parent()->GetGeneratedTNodeTypeName();
346 }
347
348 const TypeVector& parameter_types() const { return parameter_types_; }
349 const Type* return_type() const { return return_type_; }
350
351 friend size_t hash_value(const BuiltinPointerType& p) {
352 size_t result = base::hash_value(p.return_type_);
353 for (const Type* parameter : p.parameter_types_) {
354 result = base::hash_combine(result, parameter);
355 }
356 return result;
357 }
358 bool operator==(const BuiltinPointerType& other) const {
359 return parameter_types_ == other.parameter_types_ &&
360 return_type_ == other.return_type_;
361 }
362 size_t function_pointer_type_id() const { return function_pointer_type_id_; }
363
364 std::vector<TypeChecker> GetTypeCheckers() const override {
365 return {{"Smi", ""}};
366 }
367
368 bool HasContextParameter() const;
369
370 private:
371 friend class TypeOracle;
372 BuiltinPointerType(const Type* parent, TypeVector parameter_types,
373 const Type* return_type, size_t function_pointer_type_id)
374 : Type(Kind::kBuiltinPointerType, parent),
375 parameter_types_(parameter_types),
376 return_type_(return_type),
377 function_pointer_type_id_(function_pointer_type_id) {}
378 std::string SimpleNameImpl() const override;
379
380 const TypeVector parameter_types_;
381 const Type* const return_type_;
382 const size_t function_pointer_type_id_;
383};

392class V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE UnionType final : public Type {
393 public:
394 DECLARE_TYPE_BOILERPLATE(UnionType)
395 std::string GetGeneratedTypeNameImpl() const override {
396 return "TNode<" + GetGeneratedTNodeTypeName() + ">";
397 }
398 std::string GetGeneratedTNodeTypeNameImpl() const override;
399 std::string GetRuntimeType() const override {
400 return parent()->GetRuntimeType();
401 }
402 std::string GetDebugType() const override { return parent()->GetDebugType(); }
403
404 friend size_t hash_value(const UnionType& p) {
405 size_t result = 0;
406 for (const Type* t : p.types_) {
407 result = base::hash_combine(result, t);
408 }
409 return result;
410 }
411 bool operator==(const UnionType& other) const {
412 return types_ == other.types_;
413 }
414
415 base::Optional<const Type*> GetSingleMember() const {
416 if (types_.size() == 1) {
417 DCHECK_EQ(*types_.begin(), parent());
418 return *types_.begin();
419 }
420 return base::nullopt;
421 }
422
423 bool IsSubtypeOf(const Type* other) const override {
424 for (const Type* member : types_) {
425 if (!member->IsSubtypeOf(other)) return false;
426 }
427 return true;
428 }
429
430 bool IsSupertypeOf(const Type* other) const {
431 for (const Type* member : types_) {
432 if (other->IsSubtypeOf(member)) {
433 return true;
434 }
435 }
436 return false;
437 }
438
439 bool IsTransient() const override {
440 for (const Type* member : types_) {
441 if (member->IsTransient()) {
442 return true;
443 }
444 }
445 return false;
446 }
447
448 bool IsConstexpr() const override { return parent()->IsConstexpr(); }
449
450 const Type* NonConstexprVersion() const override {
451 if (!IsConstexpr()) return this;
452 return parent()->NonConstexprVersion();
453 }
454
455 void Extend(const Type* t) {
456 if (const UnionType* union_type = UnionType::DynamicCast(t)) {
457 for (const Type* member : union_type->types_) {
458 Extend(member);
459 }
460 } else {
461 if (t->IsSubtypeOf(this)) return;
462 set_parent(CommonSupertype(parent(), t));
463 EraseIf(&types_,
464 [&](const Type* member) { return member->IsSubtypeOf(t); });
465 types_.insert(t);
466 }
467 }
468 std::string ToExplicitString() const override;
469
470 void Subtract(const Type* t);
471
472 static UnionType FromType(const Type* t) {
473 const UnionType* union_type = UnionType::DynamicCast(t);
474 return union_type ? UnionType(*union_type) : UnionType(t);
475 }
476
477 std::vector<TypeChecker> GetTypeCheckers() const override {
478 std::vector<TypeChecker> result;
479 for (const Type* member : types_) {
480 std::vector<TypeChecker> sub_result = member->GetTypeCheckers();
481 result.insert(result.end(), sub_result.begin(), sub_result.end());
482 }
483 return result;
484 }
485
486 private:
487 explicit UnionType(const Type* t) : Type(Kind::kUnionType, t), types_({t}) {}
488 void RecomputeParent();
489 std::string SimpleNameImpl() const override;
490
491 std::set<const Type*, TypeLess> types_;
492};

546class AggregateType : public Type {
547 public:
548 DECLARE_TYPE_BOILERPLATE(AggregateType)
549 std::string GetGeneratedTypeNameImpl() const override { UNREACHABLE(); }
550 std::string GetGeneratedTNodeTypeNameImpl() const override { UNREACHABLE(); }
551
552 virtual void Finalize() const = 0;
553
554 void SetFields(std::vector<Field> fields) { fields_ = std::move(fields); }
555 const std::vector<Field>& fields() const {
556 if (!is_finalized_) Finalize();
557 return fields_;
558 }
559 bool HasField(const std::string& name) const;
560 const Field& LookupField(const std::string& name) const;
561 const std::string& name() const { return name_; }
562 Namespace* nspace() const { return namespace_; }
563
564 virtual const Field& RegisterField(Field field) {
565 fields_.push_back(field);
566 return fields_.back();
567 }
568
569 void RegisterMethod(Method* method) { methods_.push_back(method); }
570 const std::vector<Method*>& Methods() const {
571 if (!is_finalized_) Finalize();
572 return methods_;
573 }
574 std::vector<Method*> Methods(const std::string& name) const;
575
576 std::vector<const AggregateType*> GetHierarchy() const;
577 std::vector<TypeChecker> GetTypeCheckers() const override {
578 return {{name_, ""}};
579 }
580
581 const Field& LastField() const {
582 for (base::Optional<const AggregateType*> current = this;
583 current.has_value();
584 current = (*current)->parent()->AggregateSupertype()) {
585 const std::vector<Field>& fields = (*current)->fields_;
586 if (!fields.empty()) return fields[fields.size() - 1];
587 }
588 ReportError("Can't get last field of empty aggregate type");
589 }
590
591 protected:
592 AggregateType(Kind kind, const Type* parent, Namespace* nspace,
593 const std::string& name,
594 MaybeSpecializationKey specialized_from = base::nullopt)
595 : Type(kind, parent, specialized_from),
596 is_finalized_(false),
597 namespace_(nspace),
598 name_(name) {}
599
600 void CheckForDuplicateFields() const;
601 // Use this lookup if you do not want to trigger finalization on this type.
602 const Field& LookupFieldInternal(const std::string& name) const;
603 std::string SimpleNameImpl() const override { return name_; }
604
605 protected:
606 mutable bool is_finalized_;
607 std::vector<Field> fields_;
608
609 private:
610 Namespace* namespace_;
611 std::string name_;
612 std::vector<Method*> methods_;
613};

654enum class ObjectSlotKind : uint8_t {
655 kNoPointer,
656 kStrongPointer,
657 kMaybeObjectPointer,
658 kCustomWeakPointer
659};
660
661inline base::Optional<ObjectSlotKind> Combine(ObjectSlotKind a,
662 ObjectSlotKind b) {
663 if (a == b) return {a};
664 if (std::min(a, b) == ObjectSlotKind::kStrongPointer &&
665 std::max(a, b) == ObjectSlotKind::kMaybeObjectPointer) {
666 return {ObjectSlotKind::kMaybeObjectPointer};
667 }
668 return base::nullopt;
669}

671class ClassType final : public AggregateType {
672 public:
673 DECLARE_TYPE_BOILERPLATE(ClassType)
674 std::string ToExplicitString() const override;
675 std::string GetGeneratedTypeNameImpl() const override;
676 std::string GetGeneratedTNodeTypeNameImpl() const override;
677 bool IsExtern() const { return flags_ & ClassFlag::kExtern; }
678 bool ShouldGeneratePrint() const {
679 if (flags_ & ClassFlag::kCppObjectDefinition) return false;
680 if (flags_ & ClassFlag::kCppObjectLayoutDefinition) return false;
681 if (!IsExtern()) return true;
682 if (!ShouldGenerateCppClassDefinitions()) return false;
683 return !IsAbstract() && !HasUndefinedLayout();
684 }
685 bool ShouldGenerateVerify() const {
686 if (flags_ & ClassFlag::kCppObjectDefinition) return false;
687 if (flags_ & ClassFlag::kCppObjectLayoutDefinition) return false;
688 if (!IsExtern()) return true;
689 if (!ShouldGenerateCppClassDefinitions()) return false;
690 return !HasUndefinedLayout() && !IsShape();
691 }
692 bool ShouldGenerateBodyDescriptor() const {
693 if (flags_ & ClassFlag::kCppObjectDefinition) return false;
694 if (flags_ & ClassFlag::kCppObjectLayoutDefinition) return false;
695 if (flags_ & ClassFlag::kGenerateBodyDescriptor) return true;
696 return !IsAbstract() && !IsExtern();
697 }
698 bool DoNotGenerateCast() const {
699 return flags_ & ClassFlag::kDoNotGenerateCast;
700 }
701 bool IsTransient() const override { return flags_ & ClassFlag::kTransient; }
702 bool IsAbstract() const { return flags_ & ClassFlag::kAbstract; }
703 bool IsLayoutDefinedInCpp() const {
704 return flags_ & ClassFlag::kCppObjectLayoutDefinition;
705 }
706 bool HasSameInstanceTypeAsParent() const {
707 return flags_ & ClassFlag::kHasSameInstanceTypeAsParent;
708 }
709 bool ShouldGenerateCppClassDefinitions() const {
710 if (flags_ & ClassFlag::kCppObjectDefinition) return false;
711 if (flags_ & ClassFlag::kCppObjectLayoutDefinition) return false;
712 return (flags_ & ClassFlag::kGenerateCppClassDefinitions) || !IsExtern();
713 }
714 bool ShouldGenerateCppObjectDefinitionAsserts() const {
715 return flags_ & ClassFlag::kCppObjectDefinition;
716 }
717 bool ShouldGenerateCppObjectLayoutDefinitionAsserts() const {
718 return flags_ & ClassFlag::kCppObjectLayoutDefinition &&
719 flags_ & ClassFlag::kGenerateCppClassDefinitions;
720 }
721 bool ShouldGenerateFullClassDefinition() const { return !IsExtern(); }
722 bool ShouldGenerateUniqueMap() const {
723 return (flags_ & ClassFlag::kGenerateUniqueMap) ||
724 (!IsExtern() && !IsAbstract());
725 }
726 bool ShouldGenerateFactoryFunction() const {
727 return (flags_ & ClassFlag::kGenerateFactoryFunction) ||
728 (ShouldExport() && !IsAbstract());
729 }
730 bool ShouldExport() const { return flags_ & ClassFlag::kExport; }
731 bool IsShape() const { return flags_ & ClassFlag::kIsShape; }
732 bool HasStaticSize() const;

831class VisitResult {
832 public:
833 VisitResult() = default;
834 VisitResult(const Type* type, const std::string& constexpr_value)
835 : type_(type), constexpr_value_(constexpr_value) {
836 DCHECK(type->IsConstexpr());
837 }
838 static VisitResult NeverResult();
839 static VisitResult TopTypeResult(std::string top_reason,
840 const Type* from_type);
841 VisitResult(const Type* type, StackRange stack_range)
842 : type_(type), stack_range_(stack_range) {
843 DCHECK(!type->IsConstexpr());
844 }
845 const Type* type() const { return type_; }
846 const std::string& constexpr_value() const { return *constexpr_value_; }
847 const StackRange& stack_range() const { return *stack_range_; }
848 void SetType(const Type* new_type) { type_ = new_type; }
849 bool IsOnStack() const { return stack_range_ != base::nullopt; }
850 bool operator==(const VisitResult& other) const {
851 return type_ == other.type_ && constexpr_value_ == other.constexpr_value_ &&
852 stack_range_ == other.stack_range_;
853 }
854
855 private:
856 const Type* type_ = nullptr;
857 base::Optional<std::string> constexpr_value_;
858 base::Optional<StackRange> stack_range_;
859};

864class VisitResultVector : public std::vector<VisitResult> {
865 public:
866 VisitResultVector() : std::vector<VisitResult>() {}
867 VisitResultVector(std::initializer_list<VisitResult> init)
868 : std::vector<VisitResult>(init) {}
869 TypeVector ComputeTypeVector() const {
870 TypeVector result;
871 for (auto& visit_result : *this) {
872 result.push_back(visit_result.type());
